2026-04-13 15:22:50,939 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: The workbook has a single sheet 'Exp-DB' with 7 columns. Column 2 already contains the desired category for each transaction (e.g., 'amazon', 'Auto'). Columns 5 and 7 currently contain formulas that look up the category based on the shortened description (column 1). The instruction asks to assign categories automatically without using those lookup formulas. Therefore we will replace the formulas in columns 5 and 7 with the static category values from column 2 for every data row. We'll load the workbook, iterate over rows 2..max_row, copy the category value, write it into columns 5 and 7, and save the modified workbook to the output directory preserving the original filename. After saving, we'll reload the file with data_only=True to verify the cells contain plain values (no formulas).
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from pathlib import Path
import os

# Paths
input_path = Path(input_spreadsheet)
output_dir = Path("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet")
output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
output_path = output_dir / input_path.name

# Load workbook (keep formulas initially to read them)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # Assuming single sheet as inspected

max_row = ws.max_row
max_col = ws.max_column
print(f"Processing sheet '{ws.title}' with {max_row} rows and {max_col} columns")

# Replace formulas in column 5 (E) and column 7 (G) with static category from column 2 (B)
for r in range(2, max_row + 1):
    category = ws.cell(row=r, column=2).value  # column B
    # Write plain value (no formula) into columns E and G
    ws.cell(row=r, column=5).value = category  # column E
    ws.cell(row=r, column=7).value = category  # column G

# Save the modified workbook
wb.save(output_path)
print(f"Saved modified workbook to {output_path}")

# Verify that columns 5 and 7 now contain plain values (no formulas)
# Reload with data_only=True to read cached values
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[ws.title]

# Sample check for first few rows
samples = []
for r in range(2, min(max_row, 6)):
    samples.append((ws_check.cell(r,5).value, ws_check.cell(r,7).value))
print("Sample values (col5, col7) after replacement:", samples)
```
